3. If `nums[j] < nums[i]`, it means `nums[i]` can be appended to the LIS ending at `nums[j]`, so update `f[i]` and `cnt[i]` accordingly: if `f[i]` is less than `f[j] + 1`, update `f[i]` and `cnt[i]` to `f[j] + 1` and `cnt[j]`, respectively; if `f[i]` is equal to `f[j] + 1`, increment `cnt[i]` by `cnt[j]`.
4. After updating `f[i]` and `cnt[i]`, check if the current maximum length `mx` is less than `f[i]`, and if so, update `mx` and `ans` to `f[i]` and `cnt[i]`, respectively; if `mx` is equal to `f[i]`, increment `ans` by `cnt[i]`.
